		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I have an off-topic question to fellow Japanese learners. It&#8217;s related to learning vocab. I seem to have a problem memorizing the, well, vocab itself. For example, my card in Anki will have 教育 at the front (well, I don&#8217;t don&#8217;t do cards with isolated vocab words, but you get what I mean), and looking at it while reviewing I will remember that the word means &#8220;education&#8221;, but I won&#8217;t remember that it&#8217;s read きょういく. So I will end up failing the card over and over again and needless to say it gets really frustrating. </p>
<p>Since learning the readings of individual kanji in isolation seems to be generally discouraged, I&#8217;ve been wondering if there is a way to make the process easier, so that it doesn&#8217;t feel like banging my head against a wall.</p>
